HEADWORD: lobotomy
<hw>lobotomy</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med., Surgery)</fld> <def>The
surgical interruption of nerve tracts to and from the frontal lobe of
the brain, by cutting into the brain.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> prefrontal lobotomy, prefrontal leucotomy.</syn>⟦br⟧
